description: Barry White - Unlimited (4CD + DVD) [2009] DVD9 Barry White (born Barry Eugene Carter; September 12, 1944 – July 4, 2003) was an American singer, songwriter and composer. A three-time Grammy Award–winner known for his distinctive bass-baritone voice and romantic image, White's greatest success came in the 1970s as a solo singer and with The Love Unlimited Orchestra, crafting many enduring soul, funk, and disco songs such as his two biggest hits, "You're the First, the Last, My Everything" and "Can't Get Enough of Your Love, Babe". Unlimited presents tracks from when he stepped out with his own sound, with Love Unlimited in 1972, through his final studio album, the Grammy-winning Staying Power, released in 1999. The DVD offers every video from his tenure on A&M Records and rare bonus clips, including a live duet with Luciano Pavarotti that has become a YouTube phenomenon; each clip has bonus commentary from Jack Perry, White's longtime friend, co-producer and musical director.
